N2  -  Background: rTMS is a non‐invasive technique using magnetic coils to painlessly stimulate brain regions to influence cortical activity. DeeprTMS allows for stimulation of deeper brain structures, thereby potentially providing more significant effects on brain activity and function. rTMS studies suggest that stimulation can produce long term changes in cortical synapses akin to LTP and LTD, and might influence neuronal regulation and network patterns. In a placebo‐controlled, double‐blind, pilot study we evaluated the safety and feasibility of high frequency and low frequency deep‐rTMS to prefrontal areas of AD patients receiving stable doses of accepted AD medications. Methods: 40 participants, ages 55‐80, with mild to moderate AD according to NINCDS‐ADRDA criteria and receiving stable doses of standardADmedications were randomly divided into 3 treatment groups and received either real (10 Hz or 1 Hz) or sham rTMS treatments, in a double‐blind, placebo‐controlled fashion. Standard functional and cognitive assessments were performed at baseline, after the first 4 weeks of treatment, after the 8 week treatment period, and after an additional 8 week follow up post‐treatment. Results: A trend toward improvement was observed in both cognitive and clinical measures in patients treated with high frequency deep‐rTMS, which lasted through a 2 month, post‐treatment phase. While some cognitive improvements were noted in the low‐frequency treatment group, positive effects were less evident in clinical measures. Subjects with more advanced disease as based on cognitive scores showed more improvement with pre‐frontal stimulation, which may suggest a location‐related effect. Treatment effects were not related to changes in depressive symptoms. Conclusions: Deep‐rTMS may have therapeutic value in the symptomatic treatment of patients with AD. High frequency stimulation appears to have a more beneficial effect in this small sample, but further studies to understand the physiological mechanisms of deeprTMS action and to improve treatment parameters are warranted.
