N2  -  INTERVENTION: tNIRS+tDCS group:Transcranial near‐infrared stimulation (tNIRS) parameters: Stimulation parameters: the wavelength was 1064nm near infrared light, the energy density was 208J/cm2, the stimulation intensity was 80mW/cm2, the stimulation area was 0.24cm2 (5.5mm in diameter), and the frequency was 40Hz. Stimulation target: bilateral angular gyrus (P3, P4, international electroencephalogram 10/20 lead system); The neuronavigation system was used to accurately determine the stimulation target. Stimulation duration: bilateral simultaneous 20 minutes, lasting 6W. Transcranial direct current stimulation (tDCS) parameters Stimulation parameters: current intensity was 1.5mA; Stimulation targets: the anode was placed in the bilateral angular gyrus (P3, P4, international electroencephalogram 10/20 lead system), and the cathode was placed in the contralateral posterior ear mastoid. The neuronavigation system was used to accurately determine the stimulation target. Stimulation duration: bilateral simultaneous 20 minutes, lasting 6W.;Shame group:Using a machine that was consistent in appearance and operation with the real one, current appeared only at the beginning and the last 15 seconds of stimulation during sham stimulation. During near‐infrared light treatment, a spacer without near‐infrared light was placed in the corresponding part of the patient. The stimulation targets and duration were the same as above.; CONDITION: Alzheimers disease PRIMARY OUTCOME: Alzheimer disease assessment scale‐cog 13; SECONDARY OUTCOME: Mini‐Mental State Examination;Montreal?Cognitive Assessment;Clinical dementia rating;Digit span test;Clock drawing task;Trail making test;Auditory Verbal Learning Test;Neuropsychiatric Inventory;Pittsburgh Sleep Quality Index;Hamilton Depression Scale;Blood AD inflammatory factors and metabolomics;Functional magnetic resonance imaging + pCASL; INCLUSION CRITERIA: (1) Subjects with informed consent; (2) Right‐handed, aged 50‐80 years, male or female; (3) Meeting the core clinical criteria of probable AD dementia in the 2011 NIA‐AA revised diagnostic criteria for AD; (4) CDR <=2, 11<= MMSE <=26; (5) Positive results of plasma biomarker pTau217 (single molecule array assay, Udi Biotechnology Co., LTD.).
