N2  -  To test the feasibility of conducting a 10‐day Intermittent Theta Burst Stimulation(iTBS) repetitive Transcranial Magnetic Stimulation (rTMS) protocol twice using across‐over design in individuals with Mild Cognitive Impairment (MCI), pilot test thestudy protocol to assess study design, and collect pilot data on the effect ofstimulations over 3 different brain regions (left dorsolateral prefrontal cortex (DLPFC),lateral parietal cortex (LPC), vertex) on working memory, new‐learning and executivefunction in MCI. Neuropsychological and sleep measures, functional brain magneticresonance imaging (fMRI), high density EEG and questionnaires will be performed at 5timepoints ‐ baseline, post‐treatment after first period of 10 daily iTBS rTMS sessions,post‐washout period of 4 weeks, post‐treatment after cross‐over to second period of 10daily iTBS rTMS sessions, and 4 weeks follow‐up post‐treatment.
