N2  -  INTERVENTION: Sham rTMS group:The patient was seated in a comfortable chair with his hands rotated internally in a relaxed posture. RMT was the lowest intensity to elicit motor evoked potentials of at least 50 mV in at least five of the 10 trials in the first dorsal interosseous muscle. During daily treatment, rTMS was applied to the stimulation site using a Magstim Rapt‐2 stimulator with a 70mm thermostatic figure‐of‐eight coil, and the TMS coil was fixed tangentially to the scalp region corresponding to the main hand motor area contralateral to the target muscle. The same coil was rotated 45° away from the scalp, one side of the coil was in contact with the scalp, and the distance between the center of the coil and the target site was more than 5 cm. The patient also perceived the same noise and sensation caused by the stimulation. The stimulation location was in the left DLPFC. A total of 30 treatments were given for 6 weeks. Blood pressure and heart rate were measured before and after the intervention to ensure that the patient was well before leaving.;rTMS group:The stimulation site was again located in the left DLPFC, and the coil stem was directed 45° posterior and lateral to the sagittal plane. The distance between the center of the coil and the target site was less than 1cm, and the patients received 3 minutes and 20 seconds of uninterrupted rTMS treatment (pulse intensity of 70% resting motor threshold, 50Hz inside the plexus + 5Hz outside the plexus, 2 seconds of stimulation, 8 seconds of interval, 600 pulses each time, total stimulation time was 3 minutes and 20 seconds). All patients received rTMS 5 times a week, 3 minutes and 20 seconds each time for 6 weeks, a total of 30 times. Blood pressure and heart rate were measured before and after the intervention to ensure tha CONDITION: Alzheimer's disease PRIMARY OUTCOME: Alzheimer's Disease Assessment Scale‐Cognitive, ADAS‐cog;Montreal Cognitive Assessment, MoCA;Mini‐mental State Examination, MMSE; 