N2  -  INTERVENTION: Dose: 2 milliamperes (mA) Duration: 20 minutes per session Frequency: 10 sessions in total Electrode placement: Anodal electrode at F3; cathodal electrodes at FP1, FZ, C3, and F7 Mode of administration: Non‐invasive brain stimulation using HD‐tDCS device Setting: Administered in a clinical or research facility under supervision,Dose: 2 milliamperes (mA) Duration: 20 minutes per session Frequency: 10 sessions in total Electrode placement: Anodal electrode at FCz; cathodal electrodes at AFz, FC3, FC4, and CPz Mode of administration: Non‐invasive brain stimulation using HD‐tDCS device Setting: Administered in a clinical or research facility under supervision,Dose: 2 milliamperes for 30 seconds at start and end only (no stimulation during middle period) Duration: 20 minutes (same as active groups to maintain blinding) Electrode placement: Same as Intervention 1 (F3‐centered configuration) Mode of administration: Identical setup using HD‐tDCS device with sham protocol Setting: Administered in a clinical or research facility under supervision Experimental Device,Experimental Device,Placebo Comparator Device HD‐tDCS targeting the dorsolateral prefrontal cortex,HD‐tDCS targeting the supplementary motor area,Sham stimulation CONDITION: Motoric Cognitive Risk Syndrome; Cognitive Dysfunction; Gait Disorders, Neurologic; Transcranial Direct Current Stimulation The primary health condition studied is Motoric Cognitive Risk (MCR) syndrome, which is associated with increased risk of dementia and functional decline in older adults. ; Motoric Cognitive Risk Syndrome; Cognitive Dysfunction; Gait Disorders, Neurologic; Transcranial Direct Current Stimulation PRIMARY OUTCOME: Cognition two times, two days Montreal Cognitive Assessment total score,Cognition two times, two days Mini‐Mental State Examination total score,Executive function two times, two days Trial making test,Attention two times, two days Digital symbol modality test,Episode memory two times, two days